- @press_title = "Offerpal Media Sheds Light on Virtual Gifting, Highlights This Season's Hottest Ways to Spread Holiday Cheer Online"
- @press_subtitle = "From ornaments to stocking stuffers, millions of virtual gifts expected to be exchanged this belt-tightening holiday season"

%p
  - press_date(:fremont)
  This year, instead of looking under the tree, a whole lot of folks will be
  checking their
  #{link_to('social networking profile pages', 'http://myofferpal.wordpress.com/2008/12/01/social-apps-becoming-a-bigger-piece-of-the-pie/')}
  to see what Santa has left them. With the growing
  #{link_to('popularity of social networks', 'http://myofferpal.wordpress.com/2008/11/10/tv-down-social-networks-up/')}
  and with holiday shoppers feeling the pinch, consumers are increasingly looking to
  #{link_to('virtual gifts', 'http://myofferpal.wordpress.com/2008/09/26/redeeming-virtual-currency-in-social-applications/')}
  as a way to share the holiday spirit without breaking the bank.

%p
  Virtual gift-giving has become one of the top activities on social networks
  like Facebook, MySpace, Bebo and hi5, with the Web-wide market for virtual
  goods estimated to be at least $2 billion. Considering that the cost of most
  virtual items is one or two dollars, the number of transactions involved is
  astronomical. In many cases, virtual gifts are completely free to the sender,
  who can earn virtual currency by taking part in targeted advertising offers
  provided by #{link_to_offerpal('Offerpal Media')}, the leading &quot;Managed
  Offer Platform&quot; for social publishers.

%p
  On social networks, application developers are opening virtual holiday shops,
  selling wares appropriate to the season-everything from Christmas tree ornaments
  to Santa's reindeer. For smalltime spenders, giving a one-dollar virtual
  gingerbread house to a friend or a free virtual candy cane to a coworker
  is the perfect solution to keeping the holiday budget in check while spreading
  yuletide cheer. Developers, in turn, earn real revenues from these transactions
  through their partnership with Offerpal Media, which is the leading platform for
  social media advertising.

