%p
  Beyond virtual gift-giving, social networking applications are also being
  designed to help people get through the holidays without missing an event or
  forgetting a loved one. Social Calendar, for example, keeps track of holiday
  parties for users, while Family Builder can ensure that everyone-from the
  cousins in Paris, Texas to the aunt in Lebanon, New Hampshire-receives a holiday
  card or gift.

%p
  &quot;Giving and receiving virtual gifts with friends on social networks is one
  of the best ways to get into the holiday spirit this year,&quot; said Anu
  Shukla, CEO of Offerpal Media. &quot;Our partners in the application development
  industry have been as hard at work as Santa's elves getting their apps ready for
  the holidays, and we hope that users will find them a fun and novel way to shop.
  Not only do these gifts make less of a dent in the bank account, they are
  imaginative and inventive in ways that only the virtual world can be.&quot;

